Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of estimating back-off rates in a CSMA network to achieve a given throughput vector using free energy approximations. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT) as well as network protocols and architectures (cs.NI). The use of free energy approximations suggests that the paper may also be related to statistical inference (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the fixed point of the inverse generalized belief propagation algorithm, which is related to control systems (cs.SY) and optimization (cs.PF).
